At the time of this writing, lots of companies are building conversational UIs: Google, Apple, Microsoft, Facebook and Amazon have Now, Siri, Cortana, M and Alexa, respectively.  In smaller companies, Magic, Operator, and perhaps others are pursuing corversational UI for various applications.

One interesting thing about conversational UI is that it doesn't suffer from UI bloat.  WeChat cramming all the functionality they have into a mobile app is a remarkable accomplishment, but doing the same in a cUI is pretty easy.  This probably that there will tend to be only one-